// GAP (miscompile, confirmed 2026-07-18): a forward `goto` that jumps OVER a
// defer registration still fires that defer at scope exit. ZER's documented
// model is runtime-registration ("defer never pushed = no fire"), and a defer
// in an untaken `if` or a block-scope defer skipped by goto correctly do NOT
// fire — but a top-level function-scope defer crossed by a forward goto DOES.
//
// EXPECTED: g == 2 (only mark(2), registered at `mid:`, should fire).
// OBSERVED: g == 231 (all three defers fire: 2, then 3, then 1).
// Concrete harm: the acquire / `goto done` / `defer release()` idiom underflows
// a lock counter (release fires on the error path where acquire never ran).
// Root cause: ir_lower.c fires function-scope defers as a static set at every
// exit/goto-target block; only defers registered AFTER the goto source are
// runtime-skipped. Proper fix needs per-defer runtime "armed" flags (set at
// DEFER_PUSH, checked at fire) — the same infrastructure the plt86m guard-flag
// mechanism already uses for the fire-twice case.
u32 g = 0;
void mark(u32 v){ g = g*10+v; }
void doit() {
    goto mid;
    defer mark(1);      // skipped by goto — must NOT fire
    defer mark(3);      // skipped by goto — must NOT fire
mid:
    defer mark(2);      // registered — should fire
    return;
}
u32 main() { doit(); return g; }   // expect 2, observed 231
